Vusumuzi Khubisa (42) said he is relieved that his missing brother&rsquo;s body had been found. Sikhosiphi Khubisa from Nsuze, near Ndwedwe in KZN, disappeared almost two weeks ago.On Tuesday the 38-year-old&rsquo;s body was found naked in a cave.Vusumuzi told Daily Sun: &ldquo;My brother was last seen leaving a tavern after he was allegedly involved in a fight with five men.&ldquo;We looked for him without success. On Tuesday some boys were playing on a mountain not far from Sikhosiphi&rsquo;s home when they noticed a swarm of flies coming from a cave.&ldquo;Curious, the boys went to the cave to investigate. When they came close they picked up a terrible smell. &ldquo;They then walked into the cave and came across Sikhosiphi&rsquo;s body. &ldquo;They ran home to tell their parents, who called me.&rdquo; Cops went into the cave and found Sikhosiphi lying on his back, naked and dead. &ldquo;If it was not for the flies, we would not have found him, or we would have found him only when only his skeleton was left,&rdquo; Vusumuzi said.&ldquo;My brother had no enemies. We don&rsquo;t know what the fight in the tavern was about but we place our hope in the hands of the law.&rdquo; Police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said a case of murder was opened at Nsuze Police Station.She said Sikhosiphi&rsquo;s body was decomposed and had several gunshot wounds.No arrests have been made.